<TITLE> CUET closed up to Jan 2 over BCL clash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 16 (bdnews24.com)--The Chittagong University of Engineering and Technology (CUET) has been declared closed until Jan2, students' welfare advisor Tazul Islam said. The CUET academic council, headed by vice chancellor Shyamol Kanti Biswas, on Wednesday morning made the decision following a clash on Tuesday night between two rival groups of Bangladesh Chhatra League, Islam told bdnews24.com. No examinations will be held during the period and the students have been asked to leave the halls by 5pm, he added. Officer-in-charge of Rauzan Police Station Nikhil Mondol told bdnews24.com the clash erupted over which faction would lay wreaths the Shaeed Minar at 12:01 on Victory Day. Some seven were injured in the clash and were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital and Rauzan Upazila health complex. One of them was identified as 'Sujon', 23. A CUET teacher who wanted not to be named said the two factions are active in campus politics--one is 'Ador group' backed by Fazle Karim MP from Rauzan and the other is 'Abdul Gani group' which has the support of state minister for environment Hassan Mahmud. bdnew
